	(text "Note, the MCP23017 drives LEDs better by pulling the \nLED to ground.  Therefore, signals are inverted in \norder to \"turn on\" an LED."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 192.024 24.892 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "3dec8796-c2ed-4c32-bc31-e2a8d15ea3c2")
	)
	(text "This example circuit uses an I/O expander (MCP2317) connected via I2C interface with interrupt \non change enabled.  It could also be polled periodically for changes."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 28.448 148.844 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "55ff0040-2edc-40fd-8de0-3d53e21435ac")
	)
	(text "I had 10 LED bar displays and \nused the first 8.  Discrete LEDs\ncould also be used.  I also used\na Bourns 4116R-1-331 (330 ohm) \nresistor pack DIP.  Individual \nresistors can also be used.  A \nDIP switch is shown, but individual\njumpers to ground could be used\ninstead."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 223.266 77.216 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "6f3f3b8e-7b8b-4505-9117-7a615798b8cb")
	)
